        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 6:24AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 624 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bertha, or 16 miles south of Jasper, moving north at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bass...                           Marble Falls...
Valley Springs...                 Yardelle...
Western Grove...                  Crossroad...
Vendor...                         Gum Springs in Newton County...
Piercetown...                     Mt Judea...
Gaither...                        Carver...
Pindall...                        Cowell...
Jasper...                         Dugger...
Pruitt...                         Everton...
Hasty...                          Lurton...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 AM CDT for
north central Arkansas.</instruction>
